A 10-year-old boy won this year&rsquo;s donkey race in the second annual Faza Festival, held in Lamu East on May 24.Fahim Hussein beat 19 others in the highly contested race. The event also featured Makuti-making, food-eating and coconut-grating competitions, as well as diverse dances and exhibitions.The festival is an initiative of Lamu woman representative Shakilla Abdalla through the National Government Affirmative Action Fund (NGAAF). It is a tribute to the larger cultural festival and aims to promote culture and nurture talents.Participating communities included the Bajunis, Bonis, Giriamas, Kikuyus from Mpeketoni and Somalis. They dressed in their traditional gears and performed traditional dances, which attracted many revellers.